Simple index.js<pre><code>async function myFunction(){
    console.log("Hello World!");
}

module.exports = {
  name: "YourAddon",
  version: "1.0.0",
  author: "YourName",
  description: "My awesome add-on!",
  myFunction
</code></pre> <p>This is simple <code>index.js</code>. As you can see, <code>module.exports</code> exports <code>name</code>, <code>version</code>, <code>author</code> and <code>description</code>. These variables are important for NovaBot to have, so it can show in /reload and in console upon start.</p>

